  "page": "Horn of Winter/Theories",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table align=\"right\" width=\"180px\" style=\"float:right; margin: 0em 0em 1em 1em;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th style=\"text-align: center; background-color:#c2c2c2; font-size:12px; -moz-border-radius-topleft:10px;-moz-border-radius-topright:10px;\">&#160;Theories&#160;may&#160;be&#160;removed&#160;if&#160;...&#160;\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"font-size:11px; text-align: left; background-color:#eeeeee; font-weight:lighter;-moz-border-radius-bottomleft:10px;-moz-border-radius-bottomright:10px;padding-right: 1em; padding-left: .5em; padding-right: .5em;\">\n<ol><li>Stated as questions or possibilities.</li>\n<li>More appropriate for another article.</li>\n<li>Illogical or previously disproven.</li>\n<li>Proven by canon source, and moved to main page.</li>\n<li>Speculative and lacking any evidence to support arguments.</li>\n<li>Responding to another theory (use <a href=\"/index.php?title=Talk:Horn_of_Winter/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Talk:Horn of Winter/Theories (page does not exist)\">discussion page</a> instead).</li></ol>\n<dl><dd><ul><li><small>This does not include responses that are also standalone theories.</small></li>\n<li><small>Usage of an indented bullet does not imply the statement is a response.</small></li></ul></dd></dl>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>There is some discussion about the true whereabouts of the true <a href=\"/index.php/Horn_of_Winter\" title=\"Horn of Winter\">Horn of Winter</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#The_True_Horn\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The True Horn</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Evidence_For\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Evidence For</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Evidence_Against\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Evidence Against</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_True_Horn\">The True Horn</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Horn_of_Winter/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: The True Horn\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>It is theorized that the cracked <a href=\"/index.php/Old_warhorn\" title=\"Old warhorn\">old warhorn</a> discovered by <a href=\"/index.php/Ghost\" title=\"Ghost\">Ghost</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonglass\" title=\"Dragonglass\">dragonglass</a> cache at the <a href=\"/index.php/Fist_of_the_First_Men\" title=\"Fist of the First Men\">Fist of the First Men</a> is the true Horn of Winter.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Evidence_For\">Evidence For</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Horn_of_Winter/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Evidence For\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li>Hiding the true Horn with plenty of dragonglass would prevent the <a href=\"/index.php/Others\" title=\"Others\">Others</a> from finding it and using it to bring down the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>.</li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Fist_of_the_First_Men\" title=\"Fist of the First Men\">Fist of the First Men</a>, being (relatively) close to the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a> and a stronghold known to the Watch, is a sensible place for a former Watchman to have hidden an artifact of great power.</li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Old_warhorn\" title=\"Old warhorn\">old warhorn</a> is quite unremarkable in appearance - but there is no reason why the real horn should be anything large and extravagant. The mythical description may have been overlaid and embellished over the years.</li>\n<li>It's one of <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_Horn\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dragon Horn\">two</a> horns in the books whose purpose is not yet divined.</li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Evidence_Against\">Evidence Against</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Horn_of_Winter/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Evidence Against\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li>It does not match the mythical description of the Horn (eight feet long, etc.)</li>\n<li>No <a href=\"/index.php/Wights\" title=\"Wights\">wights</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/Others\" title=\"Others\">Others</a> paid special attention to the horn when they encountered <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Sam</a>.  Not even the lone Other that Sam came face to face with, whom he slew with an <a href=\"/index.php/Obsidian\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Obsidian\">obsidian</a> dagger.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Horn_of_Winter/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n</div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: